You Are Elmo
Sweet and innocent, you expect everyone to adore you. And they usually do!

You are usually feeling: Talkative. You've got tons of stories to tell. And when you aren't talking, you're laughing.

You are famous for: Being popular, though no one knows why. Middle aged women especially like you.

How you life your life: With an open heart. "Elmo loves you!"
The Sesame Street Personality Quiz

Your Dominant Intelligence is Musical Intelligence
Every part of your life has a beat, and you're often tapping your fingers or toes.
You enjoy sounds of all types, but you also find sound can distract you at the wrong time.
You are probably a gifted musician of some sort - even if you haven't realized it.
Also a music lover, you tend to appreciate artists of all kinds.

You would make a great musician, disc jockey, singer, or composer.
What Kind of Intelligence Do You Have?

You Are Expressionism
Moody, emotional, and even a bit angsty... you certainly know how to express your emotions.
At times, you tend to lack perspective on your life, probably as a result of looking inward too much.
This introspection does give you a flair for the dramatic. And it's even maybe made you cultivate some artistic talents!
You have a true artist's temperament... which is a blessing and a curse.
What Art Movement Are You?
You Are 52% Abnormal
You are at high risk for being a psychopath. It is very likely that you have no soul.

You are at high risk for having a borderline personality. It is very likely that you are a chaotic mess.

You are at low risk for having a narcissistic personality. It is unlikely that you are in love with your own reflection.

You are at medium risk for having a social phobia. It is somewhat likely that you feel most comfortable in your mom's basement.

You are at low risk for obsessive compulsive disorder. It is unlikely that you are addicted to hand sanitizer.
How Abnormal Are You?

So, you want the highlights of my week, eh?

Saturday:
Christa, Julia, and Tiffany came over, we went in the pool, had a squirt/ splash fight, Marco Polo, gained 12 pounds each, and watched the Phantom of the Opera. Then, we( meaning more Julia and Christa) teased Tiffany's hair. Following that, Julia took weird pictures of Christa including the one with the Tiffany "growth".

Called Shelbie. My package and collage is STILL not there, and that piss, no, ticks (Thanks a lot Christa, :P) me off. She's sending my yearbook today, HUZZAH!!


Today:
Painted my room. It's now a light blue and the paint is all over my hands.

Found yet another frog in my pool. He or she was in the bottom of my pool avoiding my Dad's attempts to get him out with the net. That's the 2nd frog this week, lol.

Went to Best Buy, found out that with my parent's deal I might be able to get a cell phone "free". My mom has yet to tell my dad about me wanting a cell phone becuase lately he's been in a "bad mood"


Off that topic, my parent's are going to the Medieval Dinner on Thursday with my daddy's workplace and I'm not allowed to come so I have no where to stay. And frankly, I don't want my Grandma to come becuase last time we had a huge fight, and since we've moved she's wanted me to go to her house everyDAY. 


I believe that is all.

The 8 year old wouldn't go inside when it was thundering and I did the "Get to the door before I count to five" trick.
WE made popsicle stick people and had a "puppet show"
Other stuff that I can't remember...

Nothing much else to post. Can't wait till Sat.
Christa call moi

Dang, I haven't written in EVER!

Crap, I forgot what I was going to write. :(

Here I am again with my ramblings.

So this week we had a 3-day weekend. It felt so much longer than three days though, but is it like that matters? :P
Friday- Cleaned. Shebe came over (well not really) and went to the mall with me. We tried on prom dresses for no reason( can never be too early, lol) and cute pants.Oh and I found the CUTEST lamp EVER!! It's a floor-lamp that looks like a spotlight!!! How awesome is that?! Then we dropped her off and I went to Katie's for Nikki's surprise party. (Ya, Nikki's the one I called a bizatch earlier... But I think she's okay now...) We ate cake and pizza (and we had cake first O_o ) then we saw Hitch. We were throwing popcorn and runts at each other and made a huge mess under our seats. We were suprised that we weren't kicked out!!! After that, we went to Nikki's and played on her trampoline till about 9 when we got scared the rapist guy on the news was coming after us, so we walked back to Katie's. Then we had make-overs and watched Scary Movie. Oh and LMAO, Sarah said that I was born in the wrong decade. LMAO!!! 80's ROCKS!!!

Saturday- Cleaned. Went to North Point with my Mom to pick up the SAME lamp becausse she wanted it. There goes it's coolness factor.

Sunday- Went to French lesson. Then went STRAIGHT to Rachel's cause our house was being showed or whatever. We talked about my party on Friday and where to go, scooter-ed, played DDR, and talked. ALOT. lol. But this has definitely been one of my best, most enjoyable visits to Rach's house.

So anyways, that was my weekend. upcoming news is:
PARTY on FRIDAY!!!- I'm having a going away/ early birthday party on Friday!! It's going to be so awesome!! We're taking a limo and driving to the mall!!!! YIPEE!!!

Hmm... I think that's it. Leave comments to show some love.

Well, time for more of the saga of me. 
I had to get my braces adjusted or whatever today, and they hurt like CRAP!! WTF did they do to my teeth?! I can barely eat!!

Chorus Festival is tomorrow!! I'm so excited!! Well, about the bus ride, not really performing. We totally suck!! I mean, don't tell that to Mrs. Sigler, but we do. The Altos are ALWAYS flat or slack off cause all of them are popular idiots, the sopranos get concieted and get WAY sharp! But anyways, on the bus I'm sitting next to Ellen and bringing my biiig green khaki bag to hold all the junk I need. Sarah and Nikki are going to sit in front of us and we'll talk the whole time, lol. But we have to wear our uniforms( white long collared shirt and pallatzo pants.. grr.. And since the pants are still way too long for me, I have to wear my uncomfortable, but pretty black and pink lined heels.) and wear them to SCHOOL?! Mrs. Beckman said we had to wear them to school!! AHHHHHHHHH!! But anyways... we're eating at Chik-fila for lunch, which is cool. And we only have to go to like 2 classes! HUZZAH! lol But we don't get back until 7:30 :(

Wednesday we have our presentation for science. Me, Kristen, and Melissa are so ready!! (Well, almost) Lol. I hope we get a good grade, though!!

Friday we have off cause it's teacher workday so they can prepare our new schedules and CONNECTIONS WILL BE LAST!!! YAY!!! lmao!!

I think that's it... for now...

Nothing much new here... Updated my Quizilla... Yup.
The SS test was so e-z!! Why was I worrying about it in the first place? Anyways, we figured out the thing for science!! YEA! lol... 
Shelbie came over today.. We didn't really do much, but it was fun anyways.
So Sarah figured out [ about my moving] this morning.. Then she told Katie and Nikki!! Ugh.. Friendship..
Anyways, when she called Nikki she said she was all "Whatever" and then Sarah said while in her cry time[she's very emotional] "Why aren't you being sympathetic?" and then Nikki's all "I had a bad day" WTF?

Oh well.
Ellen's party was yesterday. It was fun in it's own weird, random way. :D

I'm so excited about moving though!!! I've always wanted to live there [Florida] and now I will!! My new house even has a swimming pool!!

Saw the Incredibles for the second time last weekend with Nicole. Bounce and jump like a jackalope, everyone!!

that's it... I think..

So, hi again. Lol. Anyways, I'm happy cause I got a 93 on my essay in L.A. and 100 on the math test (no surprise there :D) 
Also, I have science today! YAAY! But more icky Hot Zone :( But less angry S.S. teacher!!!

I miss Ellen, she's at Allstate. :( GRR, curse friendship.

Yesterday, We had a total airhead sub in Chorus and she made us do worksheets the whole class. Ugh. Now I think I have permanent neck damage from looking down at my paper cause there's no desks in chorus. Also Yesterday I had my Social Studies Vocab Quiz. There was NO WORD BANK! Meanie. I hope I get a semi- good grade. *crosses fingers* But we're having this totally cool project coming up about Egypt!!!! *dances* 

Gah, my mom woke me up early so now I have to waste 30 minutes before I go to the bus. No fun. :P
But at last, it is Friday!!! FRIDAY FRIDAY FRIDAY! Finally! Even though this was a 4 day schoolweek, it seemed like school lasted FOREVER!

Well, I think that's it....

Oh yeah, remember that wire I had to get fixed? Well they said it has to move another centimeter!!! GRRR!!! They said it will have to stay on LONGER!!! How cruel is that?!

Ya, welll... Happy President's Day!! WHEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEE! No school, no school, no school! *dances like a nut* Sorry, I'm just spazzing out from the chocolate muffins.

 So,anyways, Ellen's coming over soon. God knows what we'll do knowing us, just a pair of insane nutcases that lover Jeremy Sumpter and Jesse McCartney. lol. Maybe we'll get past that part in Kingdom Hearts today... But who knows, we're so unpredictable.

Goshness, I forgot to do my social studies homework. Oh well, I'll do it later. :D

So, yup that's it....

Yeah, one of the springy wire things on my braces fell off so guess who has to go get it fixed? ME!!! GRRRRRR!! But hopefully they'll tell me I can get it off sooner!!! woOt woOtness!

Well, this week has been very uninteresting.

We're reading the Hot Zone in science. Completely Disgusting! Ugh, but for some reason I can't put it down.

Went to the mall. Got 3 jeans, a cute blue skirt,two sweatshirts, something for Shebe, DisneyMania3. Also went to Hot Topic and saw the new Charlie and the Chocolate Factory shirt, but it wasn't in my size!!! Had a quick glance in AE, found nothing. :P

So, that's pretty much it.
I have to go do my Social Studies vocab now :(
